    <string>Fixed: clicking "Use Terminal flow instead" inside the Quick re-login sheet crashed the popover.
Fixed: a transient redirect replay could mark a successful re-login as failed.
Fixed: rare fallback path could leak claude.ai cookies across accounts.</string>
    <key>CBReleaseKnownIssues</key>
    <string>Quick re-login depends on Anthropic's authorize URL staying stable; if it ever fails, use the Terminal fallback button in the sheet (now safe to tap).
Auto-restart after re-login obeys "Auto-kill CLI sessions" / "Auto-reload IDE after swap" — leave both off if you want manual control.
MCP hot-reload kills any in-flight Claude response and unsaved typed input — wait for idle before toggling MCP.</string>
